1
00:00:04,274 --> 00:00:15,615
We find, when Gopa Kumar
arrives in Goloka Vṛndāvan,

2
00:00:15,615 --> 00:00:19,286
his first day
in the spiritual world,

3
00:00:19,286 --> 00:00:22,030
[Day One | Spiritual World]

4
00:00:22,338 --> 00:00:24,133
it’s pretty amazing.

5
00:00:24,133 --> 00:00:25,549
And he arrives there

6
00:00:25,549 --> 00:00:30,371
after going through all the fourteen
varieties of planetary systems, 
 

7
00:00:30,371 --> 00:00:32,544
all the Vaikuṇṭhalokas, 
through Ayodhyā …

8
00:00:32,544 --> 00:00:35,124
he’s been everywhere,

9
00:00:37,264 --> 00:00:43,088
and he is 
in that divine abode,

10
00:00:48,326 --> 00:00:52,779
and when he’s searching 
for Nanda Bhavan—

11
00:00:52,779 --> 00:00:55,779
the house of Nanda Mahārāj,

12
00:00:55,779 --> 00:01:01,651
and he meets some Vrijabāsīs,
and they look so sad.

13
00:01:01,651 --> 00:01:05,713
He’s never seen anyone
this sad and pathetic in his life …

14
00:01:05,713 --> 00:01:10,781
in his lives—
he’s been everywhere!

15
00:01:14,265 --> 00:01:18,947
We have a stereotype

16
00:01:18,947 --> 00:01:23,089
that spiritual people 
should always be smiling.

17
00:01:26,039 --> 00:01:30,560
They always have 
a big smile on their face.

18
00:01:32,097 --> 00:01:33,960
Not so.

19
00:01:35,992 --> 00:01:38,591
He enters Vṛndāvan
and he’s thinking,

20
00:01:38,591 --> 00:01:44,538
“I have never seen a more
miserable group of people

21
00:01:44,538 --> 00:01:47,148
in my life … 
in my lives!”

22
00:01:47,148 --> 00:01:50,428
[Laughing]

23
00:01:53,404 --> 00:01:56,518
Imagine that—he’s reached
the highest abode,

24
00:01:56,518 --> 00:02:01,066
and he’s never seen this type
of misery upon someone,

25
00:02:01,081 --> 00:02:04,047
someone afflicted 
with this type of misery,

26
00:02:04,047 --> 00:02:07,644
and sadness, and anguish.

27
00:02:07,693 --> 00:02:09,974
So much so 
that when he will say:

28
00:02:09,974 --> 00:02:12,727
“Can you tell me where’s the house
of Nanda Mahārāj?”

29
00:02:12,727 --> 00:02:16,515
“[Gasp!]”, like, “Woah!!”

30
00:02:16,555 --> 00:02:26,560
Or others, they look like
paintings or statues.

31
00:02:27,189 --> 00:02:30,644
And he’s saying, 
“Give an indication,
 

32
00:02:30,954 --> 00:02:38,750
is it that way? Just … point, 
or something, please!”

33
00:02:39,886 --> 00:02:44,736
He can’t understand
why they’re so miserable.

34
00:02:46,854 --> 00:02:53,596
Till they see a dust cloud
off in the distance …

35
00:02:55,129 --> 00:02:59,081
It’s Kṛṣṇa, Balarām,
the cowherd boys, and the calves.

36
00:02:59,081 --> 00:03:01,001
The dust 
from the calves’ hooves

37
00:03:01,001 --> 00:03:05,711
bringing this giant 
dust cloud—goraja.

38
00:03:08,454 --> 00:03:11,946
As Gurudev said
in Govardhan,

39
00:03:11,946 --> 00:03:17,772
which is the place of aspiration
of everyone in this line,

40
00:03:17,772 --> 00:03:19,964
and Raghunāth Dās Goswāmī,

41
00:03:19,964 --> 00:03:24,264
nija-nikaṭa-nivāsaṁ dehi govardhana tvam
[Śrī Govardhana-vāsa-prārthanā-daśakam: 3]

42
00:03:24,264 --> 00:03:29,027
“Please, Govardhan,
give me shelter nearby You.”

43
00:03:29,027 --> 00:03:33,497
When the devotees were there
coughing on all the dust,

44
00:03:33,497 --> 00:03:37,480
Gurudev said, 
“But you all prayed for the dust”.

45
00:03:37,480 --> 00:03:40,550
[Laughing]

46
00:03:43,159 --> 00:03:47,224
And he said, “But you prayed
to get that dust,

47
00:03:47,244 --> 00:03:50,455
and now it 
has come to you!”

48
00:03:52,526 --> 00:03:56,241
Then he understands, 
with the approaching dust cloud,

49
00:03:56,241 --> 00:03:59,084
that the reason everyone
is so miserable:

50
00:03:59,084 --> 00:04:03,055
it’s just a typical day
in Vṛndāvan,

51
00:04:03,055 --> 00:04:06,825
and Kṛṣṇa, Balarām, 
сowherd boys, cows—

52
00:04:06,840 --> 00:04:10,169
they’ve gone
to the forest for the day.

53
00:04:10,184 --> 00:04:14,726
And the few hours,
the hours they’re gone

54
00:04:14,726 --> 00:04:22,389
is an intolerable separation
to the Vrijabāsīs.

55
00:04:22,548 --> 00:04:24,855
That’s why they’re
so miserable—

56
00:04:24,855 --> 00:04:28,371
they’re feeling separation
from Kṛṣṇa.

57
00:04:30,448 --> 00:04:35,260
So how will we understand
what is spiritual?
 

58
00:04:35,801 --> 00:04:43,111
bāhye viṣa-jvālā haya, bhitare ānanda-maya,
kṛṣṇa-premāra adbhuta carita
[Cc: 2.2.50]

59
00:04:43,111 --> 00:04:49,895
Kṛṣṇadās Kavirāj Goswāmī,
he’s saying that externally,

60
00:04:49,895 --> 00:04:54,652
it appears as though
one has been poisoned,

61
00:04:54,652 --> 00:05:00,344
while internally 
they’re relishing some,

62
00:05:00,344 --> 00:05:01,786
in the words 
of Guru Mahārāj,

63
00:05:01,786 --> 00:05:06,377
“some peculiar strange
nectarine juice.”

